added.title: Grube's Fairytales
added.description: Robin tries to teach the Titans valuable life lessons by reading them fairytales, but the others co-opt his stories and spin them into their own twisted yarns.

added.title: Garage Sale
added.description: Robin makes the other Titans sell their treasured mementos from past episodes.

added.title: Cool School
added.description: Rose Wilson escapes from prison defeating the Titans with cool one liners. Only Raven is immune to Rose's insults, and the two decide to hang out and do cool stuff together. Cyborg, Starfire and Beast Boy feel lame by comparison so they go to Cool School.

added.title: Hey Pizza!
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg try their best to slow the pizza delivery boy so they can get free pizza.

added.title: Gorilla
added.description: Beast Boy takes over as Alpha male of the Titans when he is in Gorilla-mode and Robin has to figure out how to get back on top.

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Jextra Perrestrial
added.description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: The Neighbor
added.description: When their neighbor tries to bring over a package for them, Gumball and Darwin realize they have never learned his name, and it's way too late to ask. They try everything to figure out what it is, but when they do they find out there are bigger secrets to learn about their neighbor than just his name...

added.title: The Inquisition
added.description: The students of Elmore Junior High find their world turned upside down when the mysterious school superintendent comes to stamp out their cartoonish ways. But who wants to be normal? Certainly not Gumball and Darwin.

added.title: The Knights
added.description: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

added.title: The Phone
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin get their first cell phone, they foolishly give out their number to super-intense Ocho.

added.title: The Poltergeist
added.description: Gumball and Darwin give Mr Robinson a home and end up saving his marriage.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears while trapped in a pet shop, so they can save French Fry from facing hers.

added.title: Apple's Short
added.description: Apple needs to be tall so that he can be in love.

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: The Island
added.description: While trying to sail to Japan, the Baby Bears get stranded on an island. Luckily, they meet Dave and Karla, who help with survival on the island while looking for an escape.

added.title: Baby Bears on a Plane
added.description: The Baby Bears have an adventure in the sky while aboard a plane to Sweden. But when the baby Bears are forced to sit in different sections of the plan, things get a bit haywire for everyone on board.

added.title: Yuri and the Bear
added.description: Baby Ice Bear lives alone in the arctic and meets a mysterious man named Yuri. Together they help each other survive the cold environment.

added.title: Bunnies
added.description: The Baby Bears meet a group of helpless bunnies. When they find out the bunnies live in fear of vicious crows, the Bears decide to become heroes and help out.

added.title: Panda 2
added.description: Baby Panda happily lives in a closed off environment for study. But when he's given a new friend, Panda 2, his worldview is shaken, which sets him off on a great adventure.

added.title: Lazer Royale
added.description: The Baby Bears sign up for a game of laser tag, hoping to win some ice cream. But, the round of laser tag turns out to be less of a game and more like a war zone.
The Baby Bears' dreams come true when they find a 100 dollar bill. But when they can't bear to spend it, they realize it's difficult to let go.

added.title: Baby Bears Can't Jump
added.description: In order to win a pizza, the Baby Bears play basketball against a ragtag gang of kids.

added.title: The Dark Room
added.description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

added.title: The Collector
added.description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

added.title: The Boy Who Cried Lechuza
added.description: After faking an injury to get out of work, Vic gains sympathy from everyone while unknowingly attracting attention from a dangerous mythical creature.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: Sadie Killer
added.description: Steven and the Cool Kids start a band, but they have trouble finding their sound.

added.title: Kevin Party
added.description: Kevin is throwing a party, and Steven is invited.

added.title: Lars of the Stars
added.description: Lars rises to the occasion.

added.title: Jungle Moon
added.description: Stevonnie finds themself alone on an adventure.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: Duncan Disorderly
added.description: Duncan escapes during a community walk only to discover he has to babysit Cody and Bridgette.

added.title: Soother or Later
added.description: A terrified Duncan, who's afraid of lightning, learns it's even harder to break back into school than it was to break out when he finally escapes and finds himself in a dark alley with Izzy during a thunderstorm.

added.title: Camping is In Tents
added.description: A class camping trip turns into a treasure hunt while Harold is determined to catch Bigfoot and keep everyone safe.

added.title: Mutt Ado About Owen
added.description: After accidentally hypnotizing Owen into being a dog, Harold thinks he must reverse the hypnosis to avoid going to jail.

added.title: Simons Are Forever
added.description: Duncan and Leshawna try to take advantage of Izzy's love for the game of Simon Says.

added.title: Stop! Hamster Time
added.description: Owen takes over the job of caring for the class hamster and learns that he's evil.

added.title: Driving Miss Crazy
added.description: Duncan leads Beth to believe she's broken his battery-powered bike and makes her chauffeur him around in a wagon for the day as punishment.

added.title: Weiner Takes All
added.description: After forgetting to book a Hot Diggity Doggity Dog mascot on National Hotdog Day, Chef tries to pass off an Australian man dressed as a kangaroo as a substitute.

added.title: Apoca-lice Now
added.description: When Chef brokers a truce with lice by selecting three kids to "host" them on their heads, Courtney instigates a kid vs. lice war.

added.title: Gnome More Mister Nice Guy
added.description: When the daycare gets taken over by evil gnomes, Duncan finds himself on the wrong team.

added.title: Out to Launch
added.description: While on a visit to Cape Canaveral, the Tennyson Trio are present for the inaugural launch of an experimental space plane. When Vilgax commandeers the ship, Ben must stop the baddie from weaponizing the shuttle before the countdown hits zero.

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Bon Voyage
added.description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: Screamcatcher
added.description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: When Max dozes off before a double feature, Ben and Gwen are left to save the drive-in by themselves as the evil magician Hex brings the movie monster "That" to life, and unleashes him on the unsuspecting moviegoers.

added.title: Bomzobo Lives
added.description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

added.title: Animorphosis
added.description: As the Tennyson trio dig up dinosaur fossils in the Badlands, Ben is unaware that Vilgax and Dr. Amino have teamed up to steal alien DNA from within the Omnitrix, but once extracted, Vilgax double crosses his fellow villain. Ben must now join forces with the evil doctor to have a chance to defeat the big baddie, but can Dr. Amino be trusted?

added.title: Assault on Pancake Palace
added.description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

added.title: High Stress Express
added.description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

added.title: Lucky Ducky Mug
added.description: When Adorabat and Badgerclops break Mao Mao's favorite mug, he gives them the silent treatment.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Lonely Kid
added.description: When AD has trouble making friends at school, MM tells her the story of how he made his first real friend —BB.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Try Hard
added.description: When the Sky Pirates take Mao Mao and Badgerclops hostage, it's up to Adorabat to save the day.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Scared of Puppets
added.description: Mao Mao is scared of puppets.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: The Perfect Couple
added.description: When Mao Mao accidentally breaks up the most perfect couple in Pure Heart Valley, he has to figure out how to get them back together.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: The Truth Stinks
added.description: Badgerclops smells, but Mao Mao and Adorabat don't know how to tell him.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: When they think each others' lives are easier, the heroes switch roles.

added.title: Head Chef
added.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

added.title: Orangusnake Begins
added.description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.

added.title: Grown Up Stuff
added.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

added.title: Stop the Presses
added.description: Richard's newspapers aren't selling, so his friends pull out all the stops to put the printed word back on top.

added.title: Castles and Kitties
added.description: Score Creeper traps the gang in a fantasy role playing game where they must follow a complex set of rules to win their freedom.

added.title: Corruption
added.description: The story of Zane's arrival in the Never-Realm and how he fell under the sway of the villainous Vex.

added.title: A Fragile Hope
added.description: Having discovered the terrible truth of Zane's fate, Lloyd finds himself imprisoned and alone in the clutches of the Ice Emperor.

added.title: Whatever Happened to... Rippy Roo?
added.description: Rippy Roo visits the plaza.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Dendy's Video Channel
added.description: Dendy tries to update KO's Video Channel for him, but has trouble finding something to post.

added.title: Dendy's Power
added.description: Dendy and KO discover a fun and exciting new POW Card exploit.

added.title: We've Got Pests
added.description: KO, Rad & Enid have to deal with tiny pests wreaking havoc in the bodega.

added.title: Space Creds
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want shoes.

added.title: Spacey McSpaceTree
added.description: Rigby has to pass a safety test.

added.title: Space Escape
added.description: The guys have to escape from someone bad.

added.title: El Vecino
added.description: Gumball y Darwin intentan averiguar el nombre de su vecino, el tipo de los cuernos. Pero, por accidente, develan su identidad falsa de testigo protegido.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Inquisicion
added.description: El superintendente escolar Malo visita la Secundaria Elmore para erradicar cualquier conducta caricaturesca.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: The Cake Mistake
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus eat a cake meant for someone else.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: Sadie asesina
added.description: Steven y los Chicos Geniales arman una banda, pero les cuesta encontrar un sonido propio.

added.title: La fiesta de Kevin
added.description: Kevin organizó una fiesta y Steven está invitado.

added.title: Lars de las estrellas
added.description: Lars demuestra estar a la altura.

added.title: Selva lunar
added.description: Stevonnie se encuentra solo en una aventura.

added.title: Tu mama y la mia
added.description: Steven lleva a Garnet a conocer a algunos de sus nuevos amigos.

added.title: Starter Pack
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to stop Muscle Man from messing with Thomas.

added.title: Ready to Rumble
added.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

added.title: RC Car
added.description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

added.title: Robo-UG
added.description: Uncle Grandpa builds a robot version of himself to help with his duties.

added.title: Trampoline
added.description: Mary buys a new trampoline for the family, but an accident lands her on the couch for a while. Determined to fight the boredom of being stuck indoors, she discovers her neighbor may be hiding something exciting.

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Etiquette Clarence
added.description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

added.title: Anywhere but Sumo
added.description: When Clarence realizes Sumo has made a new group of friends at his new school, he becomes jealous and confused. Will Clarence accept a school life void of Sumo, or scheme his way into making their friendship work?

added.title: Steak Me Amadeus
added.description: Mordecai wants to ask Margaret to be his girlfriend.

added.title: Blossom3
added.description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Brain Freeze
added.description: When a mysterious new ice cream flavor takes Townsville by storm, the girls suspect there might be foul play.

added.title: Bucketboy!
added.description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

added.title: Shower Party
added.description: Things get out of hand when Andrew W. K. helps Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus throw a party while Uncle Grandpa is in the shower.

added.title: Bombazobo Vive
added.description: Durante un viaje de rutina al DMV, Max toma un examen de manejo para renovar su licencia. Pero cuando Zombozo, disfrazado, se apropia del papel del instructor, Ben se convierte en alienígena para detener al malvado y salvar el viaje familiar.

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 1
added.description: The Decepticons compete to be the first to bring Megatron Optimus Prime's spark while Hot Rod chases the "Moon Cheetah."

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 2
added.description: Slipstream searches for her missing Seekers while Hot Rod's "Moon Cheetah" chase brings him unexpectedly aboard the Nemesis.

added.title: Ataque en el Palacio de los Panqueques
added.description: Cuando Gwen se inscribe en un concurso de comer panqueques en el mundialmente famoso Palacio de los Panqueques, Ben encuentra a los Bugg Bros. y debe detenerlos antes de que puedan obtener una provisión infinita del elemento que les da vida a sus creaciones: los panqueques del Palacio del Panqueque.

added.title: Trials Part 1
added.description: Following the network of GroundBridges left by the Allspark, Optimus and Megatron finally discover the Allspark, and its Guardian, Cheetor.

added.title: Expreso De Gran Estres
added.description: Durante una transmisión en vivo del nuevo tren bala transcontinental, La Grange se cuela para ganarle al tren. Pero Ben se suma a la diversión, iy no se detendrá ante nada para salir victorioso!

added.title: Trials Part 2
added.description: Cheetor attempts to judge whether Optimus or Megatron are more worthy of the Allspark, but an unexpected visitor dashes all the bots' plans.

added.title: Dark Birth Part 1
added.description: While Starscream acquires new power through the Allspark, the Autobots mistakenly assume Starscream is still under Megatron's command.

added.title: Dark Birth Part 2
added.description: The Autobots and Decepticons battle aboard the Nemesis while Starscream uses the Allspark and Vector Sigma to create new allies.

added.title: El Poder de Dendy
added.description: Dendy y KO descubren una nueva y emocionante característica de las tarjetas de poder.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Drilling Deep
added.description: At school, Aki struggles with the side effects of his newly replicated Drill Man schematics; later, as Mega Man, he learns to control his Fire Powers in thwarting Drill Man's assault on Skyraisers Inc.

added.title: Videodrone
added.description: Mega Man must stop Hypno Woman from turning the students and teachers at Silicon Central into her mindless drones.

added.title: Please Rush Home
added.description: A misunderstanding between Mega Man and Rush ends in the robo-pup running away from home, only to be reunited and reconciled during a confrontation with Wave Man.

added.title: Blaze of Glory
added.description: Mega Man and Suna must overcome a sibling dispute over what to do on their day off in order to stop Fire Man from overheating the city.

added.title: Nice on Ice
added.description: An "unscheduled" TV appearance not only lands Aki in hot water for missing class, but sets Ice Man on a misguided mission to "unite" (i.e. freeze together) every human and robot couple in the city!

added.title: Little Octi Lost
added.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: El cuarto oscuro
added.description: Tras ser rechazado por un club de fotografía, Val intenta conseguir una foto del legendario Chupacabra para demostrar su valor.

added.title: El Coleccionista
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic pierde una de las preciadas monedas de Val, Val hace un trato con un misterioso coleccionista de antigüedades para reemplazarla, pero el trato tiene consecuencias terribles.

added.title: Victor y la Lechuza
added.description: Después de fingir una lesión para no tener que trabajar, Vic se gana la compasión de todos mientras que, sin saberlo, atrae la atención de una peligrosa criatura mítica.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: Tenemos Plagas
added.description: K.O., Rad y Enid tienen que lidiar con una plaga diminuta y molesta que está desatando el caos en el almacén.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Aventura en el laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: Club de Lectura Secreto
added.description: Kelsey crea un club de lectura supersecreto para introducir a Craig y JP en las alegrías de la lectura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Atrapados en la jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: Jextra Perrestre
added.description: JP cree que puede ser de otro planeta, así que Craig trata de ayudarlo a hacer contacto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Demonios internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Mision para llevar
added.description: Kelsey guía a sus amigos en la misión más importante de la historia: buscar la comida para la cena.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Una extrana conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

added.title: Jefe de Cocina
added.description: Mao Mao se enfrenta a Colosal en una competencia para determinar si cocinar (y ser un héroe) es un arte o una ciencia.

added.title: El comienzo de Cobrangutan
added.description: Mao Mao incita a Cobrangután y a los Piratas del Cielo a convertirse en villanos verdaderamente malvados, dignos de un héroe legendario como él.

added.title: El dia del hamster
added.description: Owen toma el trabajo de cuidar al hamster de la clase y descubre que es malvado.

added.title: El Dia del Perro Caliente
added.description: Después de que olvida organizar el Día del Perro Caliente, Chef contrata a un actor disfrazado de canguro para representar al Señor Perro Salchicha Picante, creyendo que será un sustituto adecuado.

added.title: La super moto
added.description: Duncan hace que Beth crea que rompió su bicicleta impulsada a batería y hace que lo lleve de un lugar a otro en su carrito todo el día como castigo.

added.title: Apoca-piojos ahora
added.description: Cuando Chef pacta una tregua con los piojos seleccionando tres niños que los "alberguen" en sus cabezas, Courtney instiga una guerra de niños contra piojos.

added.title: #BurritoBucket
added.description: Babs loves her job at fast food restaurant Burrito Bucket, but her boss, who's fed up with her chronic lateness and bad case of scatterbrain, would love any excuse to fire her. When a bank robbery breaks out right across the street from work, Babs is torn between her role as a superhero and dutiful Burrito Bucket employee. Will she be able to save the day and keep her job all in the nick of time?

added.title: #MeetTheCheetah
added.description: Barbara Minerva is super-jealous of  "little Miss Perfect" Diana Prince. But when she uses an ancient artifact from her dad's collection to place a curse on Diana, it turns out that Diana's not the one who's cursed. It's Barbara.

added.title: Home on the Run/Top Slot
added.description: Home on the Run: We are introduced to Shun's mysterious backstory, his relationship with his industrialist father and desire for a closer knit family./Top Slot: Dan and Shun butt heads on how best to make the AO a real team amidst growing threats including the mysterious Shargo Ronin.

added.title: Fathers and Friends/Midsummer Nightmare
added.description: Midsummer Nightmare: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream./Father's and Fiends: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

added.title: Dawn Before Dusk
added.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 1
added.description: Sgt. Night publicly criticizes Dr. Light's views on human & robot unity during a school assembly, invoking the ire of Fire Man and forcing Silicon City's newly minted hero, Mega Man, to intervene.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 2
added.description: Mega Man stops Fire Man by replicating his powers and fighting fire with fire. Unfortunately, Mega Man also learns that he can replicate a robot's mental state as well, and must get his own anger under control to win. Defeated, Fire Man reports back to his secret master, Sgt. Night!

added.title: Panic in the Lighthouse
added.description: When Chaotique breaks into Dr. Light's lab, Mega Man must shut down his frenemy and the lab's defenses before either of them gets destroyed!

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 1
added.description: Lord Obsidian unites the Robot Masters against Mega Man and his family for an epic showdown at the Lighthouse.

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 2
added.description: As Dr. Light and Suna turn the Robot Masters against each other, Mega Man defeats and unmasks his arch nemeses, Lord Obsidian, who turns out to be Sgt. Night in disguise, and finally learns the identity of Namagem, Mega Man's long lost twin brother!

added.title: Sea of Tranquility Part 1
added.description: Optimus Prime and the Autobots battle Megatron and the Deceptions on Earth's Moon.

added.title: Sea of Tranquility Part 2
added.description: The Autobots struggle to stop the Decepticon's planet-cracking weapon as it targets Earth.

added.title: Bad Moon Rising Part 1
added.description: Starscream makes a play for leadership of the Deceptions as the Autobots storm the Decepticon's Moon Base.

added.title: Bad Moon Rising Part 2
added.description: The Autobots work to stop the Moon from crashing into the Earth as Starscream must reckon with betraying Megatron.

added.title: The Visitor Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee searches for any information his fellow Autobots might have regarding a strange creature he saw on the Moon.

added.title: The Visitor Part 2
added.description: Dino-Mode Grimlock careens out-of-control around the Ark after drinking Wheeljack's hyper-fuel.

added.title: Despeguemos
added.description: De excursión en Cabo Cañaveral, el trío Tennyson presencia el lanzamiento inaugural de una nave espacial experimental, pero cuando Vilgax comanda la nave, Ben debe impedir que el villano use el transbordador como arma antes de que la cuenta regresiva llegue a cero.

added.title: Batalla en El Biggie Box
added.description: Ben y Billy Billions se enfrentan por un set de sumo exclusivo que se vende únicamente en el centro comercial más grande del mundo, isolo para descubrir que Simon Sez, de apenas seis años, lo compró primero! Así se desata una batalla dentro de una tienda que parece tenerlo todo excepto una salida fácil de encontrar.

added.title: Desastre en Mascota
added.description: Frustrado su intento de conseguir una foto con cada mascota de vidriera, Ben y Gwen se escabullen de noche para tomarse su foto con el tótem del oso de madera... iy descubren que él y las demás mascotas cobraron vida!

added.title: #LaCubetaDeBurritos
added.description: A Babs le encanta su trabajo en el restaurante de comida rápida "La Cubeta de Burritos" , pero a su jefe, que está harto de que ella siempre llegue tarde y de su enorme dispersión, le encantaría encontrar cualquier excusa para despedirla. Cuando se produce un robo a un banco que está enfrente de su trabajo, Babs no puede decidir si encarnar su papel de superheroína o el de empleada obediente de La Cubeta. Pero ¿será capaz de salvar a todos y conservar su empleo justo a tiempo?
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #ConoceAGuepardo
added.description: Barbara Minerva está super celosa de la "pequeña señorita perfecta" Diana Prince. Pero cuando usa un antiguo artefacto de la colección de su padre para lanzar una maldición contra Diana, la maldición se vuelve en su contra.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Huyendo de casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un verdadero lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Pesadilla de verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: El chico del 3030
added.description: Los niños conocen a un misterioso niño del futuro y tratan de ayudarlo a completar su misión.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Carrera en el Arroyo
added.description: Una carrera de alta velocidad con un premio de alto riesgo puede ser demasiado para Craig y sus amigos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Verdad Apesta
added.description: Colosal huele mal, pero Mao Mao y Adorabat no saben cómo decírselo.

added.title: Dia de Intercambio
added.description: Cuando los héroes creen que la vida del otro es más sencilla, intercambian sus papeles.

added.title: Los ruidos perrunos de Owen
added.description: Después de hipnotizar accidentalmente a Owen y hacerle creer que es un perro, Harold cree que debe revertir la hipnosis para evitar ir a la cárcel.

added.title: Un Dragon en la Guarderia
added.description: Duncan finalmente logra escapar solo para descubrir que ha olvidado su chupete y necesita entrar a la escuela para recuperarlo.

added.title: Acampar es en tiendas: Segunda parte
added.description: Un viaje de campamento se convierte en una búsqueda del tesoro cuando Harold está decidido a atrapar a Pie Grande y mantener a salvo a todos.

added.title: Duncan liberado
added.description: Duncan se escapa durante un paseo en la comunidad solo para descubrir que tiene que cuidar a Cody y Bridgette.

added.title: Acampar es en tiendas: Primera parte
added.description: Un viaje de campamento se convierte en una búsqueda del tesoro cuando Harold está decidido a atrapar a Pie Grande y mantener a salvo a todos.

added.title: Simon por siempre
added.description: Duncan y Leshawna tratan de aprovecharse del amor de Izzy por el juego de Simón Dice.

removed.title: Pequena graduacion
removed.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

removed.title: Follow Your Dreams
removed.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

removed.title: Positive Attitude Theory
removed.description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

removed.title: #SuperWho?
removed.description: Overwhelmed by the amount of Superman coverage in Metropolis, Supergirl decides to get out there and really show the city what she can do. But when Superman inadvertently puts everyone in harm's way, Supergirl has to decide whether to do what's good for the people or what's good for her ego.

removed.title: #Beeline
removed.description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

removed.description: After a battle with the Mutants, Jackalman gets confused and accidentally returns to the Cats' Lair with the Thundercats, he is the dumbest mutant. Jackalman pretends to be a Thundercat so his enemies won't catch him and the Thundercats pretend to play along because they feel bad for him!

removed.description: Nya, Jay, Cole and Kai face off against the Ice Emperor's dreaded dragon, while Lloyd and his newfound allies, Kataru and Grimfax, confront the Ice Emperor himself.
